Focal and perivascular lymphoplasmocytic infiltrates were mainly found in omentum and leptomeninx (Fig. 6
); perivascular infiltrations were also seen occasionally in the brain of cats with granulomatous leptomeningitis (Fig. 7
(a)). Some of the plasma-cells stained positive for coronavirus-specific antibodies (Fig. 6(b) and 7(a)). Macrophages and T- cells comprised a minority; neutrophils were rarely observed.
